At 2.728s starting
Legend:
	Comma separated list specifies waypoint for BRISC, NCRISC, TRISC0, TRISC1, TRISC2
	BRISC is main processor, others are subordinates
	I=initialization sequence
	W=wait (top of spin loop)
	R=run (entering kernel)
	D=done (finished spin loop)
	X=host written value prior to fw launch

	A single character status is in the FW, other characters clarify where, eg:
		NRW is "noc read wait"
		NWD is "noc write done"
	rmsg(BRISC host run message): D/H device/host dispatch; NOC ID; I/G/D init/go/done; | separator; enable flags UPPER=enabled, lower=disabled: B/b=BRISC N/n=NCRISC T/t=TRISC
	smsg(subordinate run message): I/G/D for subordinate processors
	k_ids: kernel IDs per processor (ID map to file at end of section)

